A. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design Low-Level Design for Vending Machine.

Requirements:

Users can select a product and insert money (coins/notes).
Machine should display available products with their prices.
Machine should accept money, calculate change, and dispense the selected product.
Support multiple products with different prices.
Handle cases like insufficient money, out of stock, and exact change.
Support basic operations: Insert coin, Select product, Dispense item, Return change.

Constraints:

In-memory implementation is acceptable.
Focus on core transaction flow.
Support multiple denominations of coins/notes.

Edge Cases:

Insufficient balance.
Product out of stock.
User cancels the transaction.
Machine has no change left.

B. HAPPY PATH STORY

=> Rahul approaches a Vending Machine. He sees "Coke" priced at ₹25 and "Water" at ₹15.
=> He inserts a ₹50 note. He selects "Coke".
=> The machine accepts the money, dispenses a Coke bottle, and returns ₹25 as change.
=> Later, another user inserts ₹10 for a ₹15 Water bottle.
=> The machine shows "Insufficient balance" and returns the ₹10.
=> This covers: Money insertion, product selection, validation, dispensing, and change return.

